---
import Chapter from '../layouts/Chapter.astro';
const lds = [{"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList", "itemListElement": [{"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Selling", "item": "https://patrick.realestate/selling"}]}];
---
<Chapter
  title="Selling — Patrick Milhaupt · North Shore"
  description="A six-step seller's practice — provenance research, reconciliation pricing, long-form photography, ZenList pre-market window, MLS choreography, and closing discipline."
  path="/selling" current="/selling" palette="0.50"
  jsonLd={lds.length>=1 ? lds[0] : null}
  rail={[{"id": "ch-00", "num": "00", "label": "Opening"}, {"id": "ch-01", "num": "01", "label": "The Practice"}, {"id": "ch-02", "num": "02", "label": "Marketing"}, {"id": "ch-03", "num": "03", "label": "Begin"}]}
>


  <section class="chapter" id="ch-00" data-chapter="0" data-palette="0.15">
    <div class="inner" style="text-align:center; align-items:center;">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <span class="hashmark"><i></i></span>
        <div class="meta" style="border:0; padding:0;">
          <span class="eyebrow">Selling &middot; North Shore</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h1 class="headline" data-headline="">
        A seller's <em>discipline</em>.
      </h1>
      <p class="body fade-up" style="margin: 0 auto; text-align:center;">
        A representation practice refined across more than fifteen years across institutional real estate and luxury brokerage. Provenance research, architectural narrative, photography choreography, pricing reconciliation &mdash; each step carries its own checklist, its own choreography, its own <strong>discipline</strong>. <em>Curatorial</em> restraint applied at every stage.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <a class="btn" href="#ch-01">Walk through the six steps &darr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-01" data-chapter="1" data-palette="0.35">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up">
        <span class="num">01</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Chapter One</span>
          <span class="sub">The Practice</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Provenance to <em>close</em>.
      </h2>
      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step"><span class="n">STEP &middot; 01</span><div><div class="t">Provenance &amp; Architectural Research</div><div class="d">Original architect, build date, ownership chain, restoration history, comparable sales of similarly authored homes. The storied narrative your buyer will read on the listing is built here.</div></div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="n">STEP &middot; 02</span><div><div class="t">Reconciliation Pricing</div><div class="d">Three independent methods &mdash; sales comparison, replacement cost, income-equivalent. The number we bring to market is the one all three agree on.</div></div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="n">STEP &middot; 03</span><div><div class="t">Photography &amp; Long-form Narrative</div><div class="d">Golden-hour exterior, twilight pool, interior across two weather days. Five hundred words of architectural narrative, written by me. No bullet points.</div></div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="n">STEP &middot; 04</span><div><div class="t">ZenList Pre-Market Window</div><div class="d">Seven to ten days of private exposure inside the Sotheby's pre-MLS network before public listing &mdash; frequently enough to introduce the right buyer before the home ever reaches broad market.</div></div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="n">STEP &middot; 05</span><div><div class="t">MLS &amp; Open-House Choreography</div><div class="d">When we go to broad market: three open houses across three weather conditions, two private brokers' opens, and a curated invite list of forty Sotheby's advisors with active matched buyers.</div></div></div>
        <div class="step"><span class="n">STEP &middot; 06</span><div><div class="t">Closing Discipline</div><div class="d">Attorney review, inspection negotiation, appraisal defense, closing-day audit. Forty-nine line items on the closing checklist. None of them skipped.</div></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-02" data-chapter="2" data-palette="0.65">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up">
        <span class="num">02</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Chapter Two</span>
          <span class="sub">Marketing Footprint</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Local discipline.<br>Global <em>reach</em>.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        A Sotheby's International Realty listing is syndicated through the global Sotheby's network of <strong>1,100+ offices across 86 countries and territories</strong>, with distribution no listing flyer reaches &mdash; the Wall Street Journal's Mansion section, the New York Times, the Financial Times, Architectural Digest. The marketing footprint isn't an after-thought; it's the reason a storied home in Lake Forest can find its buyer in London, Singapore, or San Francisco.
      </p>
      <p class="body fade-up">
        The footprint a represented listing receives: the Wall Street Journal Friday <em>Mansion</em> section (Sotheby's exclusive ad partnership), The New York Times, the Financial Times, Architectural Digest, Mansion Global, Bloomberg, Dwell, Elle D&eacute;cor, Nikkei &mdash; plus the only real-estate app on Apple TV, the <em>RESIDE</em>&reg; flagship print magazine, the <em>Houseguest</em> video series, the Extraordinary Living Blog, the annual <em>Luxury Outlook</em>&reg; Report, and the Google Display Network. In 2024, Sotheby's videos played 65 million times across YouTube alone.
      </p>
      <div class="kpi-grid">
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">Global Network</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">1,100+ offices</span><span class="d">Across 86 countries &amp; territories</span></div>
        <div class="kpi pop"><span class="l">2025 Global Volume</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">$182.4B</span><span class="d up">+9.3% YoY in the U.S. (vs. NAR +2.6%)</span></div>
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">Site Visits 2025</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">~42M</span><span class="d">15 languages &middot; 49% from outside the U.S.</span></div>
        <div class="kpi"><span class="l">Referral Volume 2025</span><span class="v" style="font-size:22px;">~$7B</span><span class="d up">Through the global referral network</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="chapter" id="ch-03" data-chapter="3" data-palette="1.00">
    <div class="inner" style="text-align:center; align-items:center;">
      <div class="ch-head fade-up" style="justify-content:center;">
        <span class="num">03</span>
        <div class="meta">
          <span class="eyebrow">Begin</span>
          <span class="sub">A 30-minute call</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="headline" data-headline="">
        Walk through your <em>number</em>.
      </h2>
      <p class="body fade-up" style="margin: 0 auto; text-align:center;">
        Thirty minutes. A reconciliation-pricing read on your home, the live market it would launch into, and a discerning conversation about timing. No pitch.
      </p>
